      </h1>
      <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-ink-muted); font-style: italic; max-width: 55ch; line-height: var(--leading-normal);">
        The Freethinking Times has no parent company, no institutional backer,
        and no advertising revenue. It runs on time, conviction, and reader support.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">

      <h2>Why This Matters</h2>

      <p>Most journalism you encounter is subsidized by something. Legacy outlets are owned by corporations or billionaires with interests to protect. Digital media runs on advertising revenue that rewards engagement over accuracy. Platforms optimize for what keeps you scrolling, not what helps you understand.</p>

      <p>The Freethinking Times is subsidized by nothing except the belief that honest, adversarial, intellectually serious journalism is worth doing. That means it runs on an honest scarcity: there are only so many hours, and investigative work — the kind that requires FOIA requests, primary sources, and the willingness to sit with a story until it's right — takes time that has to be paid for somehow.</p>

      <p>Reader support is how independent journalism pays for itself without compromising what it's for.</p>

      <h2>What Your Support Makes Possible</h2>

      <p>Concretely: more investigative pieces, which take longer to report and write. Better sourcing, which sometimes means paying for access to databases and documents. The ability to turn down work that would create conflicts of interest. And the time to get things right rather than fast.</p>

      <p>There are no tiers, no paywalls, and no members-only content. Everything published here is free to read. Support is not a transaction — it is an act of alignment with a kind of journalism you want to exist in the world.</p>

    </div>

