      {# Other ways to help #}
      <div class="article-body">
        <h2>Other ways to help</h2>

        <p><strong>Share specific pieces.</strong> When an article is worth reading, send it to one person who would find it genuinely useful. Not broadcast — targeted. A good article landing in front of the right reader is worth more than a hundred passive impressions.</p>

        <p><strong>Link to us.</strong> If you write, blog, or maintain any kind of online presence, linking to pieces you found valuable is how independent publications build the search presence that brings new readers.</p>

        <p><strong>Write a letter.</strong> Reader correspondence published in the Letters section is part of the publication's editorial content. A thoughtful response to something we've published — sent to <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a> — contributes to the work directly.</p>

        <p><strong>Tell us what we're missing.</strong> The best editorial tip is a story that matters and isn't being told. If you know of something that deserves investigation, <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">write to the editors</a>.</p>
